'''Uneo ni Masu Takehaniyasu Shrine''' (畝尾坐健土安神社) is a Shinto shrine located in {{ill|Kashihara, Nara|ja|橿原市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}, Japan. It is situated at the northwestern foothills of {{ill|Mount Amanokagu|ja|天香具山|12=draft|12=draft}}. To the southwest, adjacent to the shrine, stands another {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Uneo Tsutamoto Shrine|ja|畝尾都多本神社|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the year 1446 (Bunan 3), the shrine was recorded in the ''Washū Five Districts Shrine Registry'' (和州五郡神社神名帳大略注解) as one of the "Four Shrines of Amanokagu" (天香山坐四處神社), alongside {{ill|Amanokaguyama Shrine|ja|天香山坐櫛真命神社|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Sakado Shrine (Amano-Iwato Shrine)|ja|坂門神社 (天岩戸神社)|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Uneo Tsutamoto Shrine|ja|畝尾都多本神社|12=draft|12=draft}}<ref>[https://genbu.net/data/yamato/tutamoto_title.htm Uneo Tsutamoto Shrine]</ref>.

